						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">dougeff wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">1. Can you simulate this overscan loss in an emulator?</div><br />In FCEUX for Windows, Config &gt; Video has two fields for NTSC scanline range, defaulting to 8-231. When testing for overscan compliance, set it to 16-228, or just run your games in the scaled mode of PocketNES (which is hardcoded to 16-228).<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"> Would a modern TV (digital) have the same edge loss with a real NES?</div><br />My Vizio VX32L shows roughly lines 8-231, the same lines that NES emulators show by default in NTSC mode.</div>

					
